    <body>
      <head>Felix Maria Gatz</head>
      <div>

        <p>German conductor.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p>Gatz was an early protagonist of the music of <ref cRef="entity-000104">Anton
            Bruckner</ref>, performing many of his works and recording his <title level="m">Te
            Deum</title>. He was a professor at the <ref cRef="entity-002591">Vienna
            Conservatory</ref> from 1929 to 1932, teaching music aesthetics, and author of
          <title level="m">Musik-Ästhetik in ihren Hauptrichtungen</title> (Stuttgart: F. Enke, 1929). </p>
      </div>

